1. keyboard shortcuts
full Cheat-Sheet in my notes...

     1.1 top
     default:
cmd+n , new setters/getter etc
cmd+shift+f - find in project
cmd+b - find usages
alt+f7 - find usages
cmd+o - find class / symbol
alt+cmd+o - find file
shift+shift twice shift- find in all
cmd+e - recent files

select and shift+f6 - refactor
select method, cmd+P - signature
mine:
alt+x - gvim
/** + then pressing Enter above a method signature will create Javadoc stubs for you
ctrl+\ - find usages
ctrl+ ] - list usages

shift+cmd+enter - copmplete if, while try-catch etc
ctrl+space - completion

     1.2 Debug

     1.3
2. Vim mode

     2.1  Install ideavim
cmd+, then plugins, search vim, install IdeaVim

configure it in ~/.ideavimrc

     2.2 Launch external vim

cmd+, then tools, external tools, +
give path to gvim and as argument $FilePath$

last, cmd+, then keymap, search vim, select tool and hit the pencil icon (add keyboard shortcut). set alt+x.

